<HEADLINE>
<P>
12 KILLED IN CRASH OF S. KOREAN COPTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEOUL 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A commercial helicopter developed engine trouble and plunged into the sea 
Thursday off the South Korean coast, killing at least 12 of 20 people aboard, 
official news reports said. 
</P>
<P>
The Korean Broadcasting System said three crew members and three passengers 
were rescued, but the others, mostly vacationers, were trapped in the aircraft. 
Two were missing. 
</P>
<P>
The bodies of the 12 were recovered from the Sikorsky copter, which was towed 
to Ullung Island off the southeast coast, the state-run television said. The 
report said no foreigners were aboard. 
</P>
</TEXT>
