<HEADLINE>
<P>
GREENPEACE PLANS TO BLOCK MISSILE TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Leaders of the international environmental group Greenpeace said Thursday they 
would sail two vessels into a military test area off Florida in an effort to 
disrupt a test launch of a Trident 2 missile from a submerged submarine, which 
they said is scheduled for today. 
</P>
<P>
The first submarine launch of a three-stage, 126,000-pound Trident 2 ended in a 
spectacular failure in March when a malfunction in the missile's nozzle system 
sent the $26.5-million rocket cartwheeling out of control seconds after launch. 
</P>
<P>
The Navy does not discuss such tests, typically conducted about 50 miles east 
of Cape Canaveral, before they take place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
