<HEADLINE>
<P>
DEBATE OVER RAIL LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Offerings for sale of Southern Pacific and Santa Fe rail line rights of way is 
a timely opportunity that should not be missed by the Los Angeles 
Transportation Commission. 
</P>
<P>
These rights of way can provide a nucleus for development of a modern rail mass 
transit system throughout the county that is critical to our area's future, 
moving large numbers of people efficiently, helping reduce air pollution and 
preventing gridlock. 
</P>
<P>
The former Pacific Electric Red Car rail system utilized some of these same 
rights of way, and was excellent, fast and efficient and provided the needs for 
many commuters. 
</P>
<P>
The dismantling of the rail service was initiated and completed by the 
shortsighted greed of special interests, which was later confirmed by 
congressional inquiry. 
</P>
<P>
For those concerned with the noise factor, may I point out, modern rail 
technology offers a quieter mode of transportation than automobiles, buses, 
trucks and motorcycles. 
</P>
<P>
JACK KRIEGER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
