<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Minnesota Vikings' attempt to acquire quarterback Steve Walsh, a St. Paul 
native, from the Dallas Cowboys has failed because the Cowboys' asking price 
was too high, said Viking General Manager Mike Lynn. 
</P>
<P>
"We're done negotiating with them," Lynn said. "It appears at this stage Walsh 
is going to be a Cowboy. He will not be a Viking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
