<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA COUNCIL VOTES TO HIRE LOBBYIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Clarita City Council, saying it wants to build up the young city's 
political muscle, has hired a lobbyist to represent the city in Los Angeles, 
Sacramento and -- if need be -- Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The council agreed Tuesday night to retain Capital Representation Group, a 
Sacramento-based firm, for $5,000 a month. 
</P>
<P>
One of the first issues the lobbyists will tackle will be proposals by a refuse 
firm and the city and county of Los Angeles to open a dump in Elsmere Canyon, 
two miles east of Santa Clarita. 
</P>
