<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wynn's International Inc. reported a 42% increase in net income for the second 
quarter, to $1.7 million from $1.2 million for the like quarter last year. 
Sales decreased 13%, to $70.5 million from $80.6 million. The company 
attributed the decline to significantly lower sales at its automotive 
air-conditioning subsidiary, due to the nationwide drop in new car and truck 
sales. Net income for the first six months totaled $4.9 million, which included 
a gain of $1.4 million from the sale of the company's interest in a joint 
venture. For the first half of 1988, net income was $990,000, which included a 
charge of $1 million for costs associated with management changes and 
termination of the company's Supplemental Retirement Plan. Net sales for the 
first six months of 1989 dropped 5%, to $143.6 million from $150.8 million for 
the comparable 1988 period. Wynn's, headquartered in Fullerton, is a supplier 
of automotive air conditioners, O-rings, seals, molded rubber products, 
petrochemical specialties products and builders hardware. 
