<TEXT>
<P>
A state judge refused to issue a temporary injunction that would have halted 
all Little League playoff games in Texas pending the outcome of a lawsuit. 
State District Judge Arthur Lesher denied the requested freeze, meaning the 
games will continue as scheduled, attorney Blaise Heaney said. 
</P>
<P>
The suit was filed by James R. King Jr., father of a player, who was upset that 
another team was not disqualified from the playoffs even though a team member 
was not eligible to play. 
</P>
