<P>
A Miami-area man accused of operating the largest clandestine steroid 
laboratory in the country was sentenced to 22 months in federal prison. U.S. 
District Judge William Hoeveler also put Justin Rogers Routt, 29, on probation 
for three years and fined him $2,000. 
</P>
<P>
Routt pleaded guilty shortly after his April arrest to conspiracy, mail fraud 
and adulteration and misbranding of prescription drugs. The Food and Drug 
Administration charged that Routt produced both steroids and inert substances 
that were sold as steroids. 
</P>
<P>
Federal agents who raided Routt's lab and warehouses found about $2 million 
worth of bulk and finished steroid products and labels for shipping nationally. 
