<P>
State Has Until Noon to Challenge Bond: The U.S. 9th Circuit Court of Appeals 
has given the state until noon today to challenge a $16.3-million bond 
requirement for a U.S. Supreme Court appeal of the merger of the Lucky and 
Alpha Beta market chains. The court told California Atty. Gen. John Van de Kamp 
