<P>
MCI, Visa in Venture: Visa U.S.A and MCI Communications Corp. announced that 
beginning Oct. 1 Visa card account numbers also will serve as MCI long-distance 
calling numbers. Holders of Visa cards will be able to call from any phone in 
the United States to nearly anywhere in the world, with monthly charges billed 
as one line on their Visa accounts. MCI will provide a separate, itemized 
billing. Tim Price, MCI's vice president for sales, said the service will be 
phased in over the next 18 months and will be available automatically to any 
Visa cardholder by the end of 1990. 
