<P>
FIRE ROUTS 9,500, KILLS 1 IN NORTHERN MYANMAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
YANGON, Myanmar 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fire swept through the city of Mandalay in northern Myanmar, formerly Burma, on 
Thursday, destroying more than 1,500 houses, leaving 9,500 people homeless and 
killing one person, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
An unspecified number of people suffered minor injuries in the blaze, according 
to the officials. There was no indication of the cause of the blaze. 
