<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARKEY WILL MISS REST OF SEASON AFTER SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Harkey underwent arthroscopic surgery on his right knee Thursday and the 
Chicago Cubs said the former Cal State Fullerton pitcher will be sidelined the 
rest of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Harkey, who was 2-7 at Triple-A Iowa with a 4.43 earned-run average in 12 
starts, will begin pitching again in October. Harkey was scheduled to be in the 
Cubs' starting rotation last spring but failed to make the team in spring 
training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
