<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALMANAC / SURVEY OF COUNTY OFFICE SPACE: CENTRAL COUNTY LEADS AIRPORT AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Central Orange County edged the John Wayne Airport area in net absorption of 
office space in the first half of 1989, according to a Grubb &amp; Ellis 
survey. The two regions accounted for 72% of the county's first-half total of 
1.7 million square feet of absorbed space, which the broker defines as square 
footage occupied by tenants minus square footage vacated. 
</P>
<P>
But while developers are busy providing new space in the airport region, 
hammers and saws are gathering cobwebs in the central county. Grubb &amp; Ellis 
said only 81,155 square feet of office space is under construction in central 
county, contrasted with 3.3 million in the airport region and 5.1 million 
countywide. 
</P>
<P>
The lack of construction in central county will "further tighten the 
availability of space in the near term," said Tom Stilley of Grubb &amp; Ellis' 
Anaheim office. Still, the central county's 23% vacancy rate was higher than 
the countywide rate of 21%. The central county has been a focal point of office 
construction in recent years. And the broker said more than 5 million 
additional square feet of space is planned for that region -- nearly half the 
10.3 million square feet planned countywide. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
