<TEXT>
<P>
The opposition leader in Myanmar, formerly Burma, has been on a hunger strike 
since the country's military leaders placed her under house arrest eight days 
ago, Western diplomats said today. 
</P>
<P>
They said Aung San Suu Kyi, secretary of the National League for Democracy, 
