<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
LEMOND TO SKIP 2 WORLD CUP RACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg LeMond, newly crowned Tour de France champion, will skip the next two 
World Cup cycle races in Britain and Canada, his team director said today. 
</P>
<P>
Team director Jose de Cauwer said the American will miss Sunday's Summer 
International in Britain and next week's Grand Prix des Ameriques in Canada 
because he wanted to take it easy for a while after his thrilling Tour de 
France victory last Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Instead of riding the Summer International in Newcastle, LeMond will take part 
in a small race in Bilzen, Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
De Cauwer said LeMond will return to the World Cup circuit Aug. 12 for the San 
Sebastian classic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
