<P>
TOP HIGH JUMPER TO COMPETE IN L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Javier Sotomayor of Cuba, the world record-holder in the high jump, will 
compete in the Jack in the Box track meet at UCLA's Drake Stadium on Aug. 6, it 
was announced today. 
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor, 23, cleared 7-11 1/2 last summer to set the world record in the high 
jump. Others entered in the event are Hollis Conway, the silver medalist in the 
Seoul Olympics, and Brian Stanton, another U.S. Olympian. 
</P>
